  "prompt": "Is there a way to see someones likes on instagram?",
  "response": "No, you can't view someone else's \"likes\" on Instagram directly. Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see the posts that others have liked. You can see the likes on your own posts and the likes on public posts if you go to the post itself, but for private accounts, you won't have access to their likes unless you are following them and they have not restricted their account.\n\nIf you're looking for posts that someone has liked, you could potentially see them if you view their activity through mutual interactions, comments, or shared posts, but there isn\u2019t a straightforward way to browse their likes through Instagram's interface. Always remember to respect privacy and follow ethical guidelines when using social media.",
